text:
California's National Guard stands ready, willing, and able to support humanitarian work in Ukraine.

Yet bureaucratic hurdles prevent them from doing so.

@SecDef and @SecBlinken must approve the required authorities so the Guard can do more to ease Ukraine's suffering. https://t.co/wPznrE4hFw

Putin's unprovoked war against Ukraine demands further action. 

Banning the sale of Russian oil and gas to the U.S. will further increase pressure on Russia’s economy.

@POTUS and Congress will keep driving up the costs on Putin until he ends this monstrous war of aggression.

@davidhogg111 You’re absolutely right.

Ending the filibuster needs to be the first order of business. 

It stands in the way of major action on everything - anything - including ending gun violence.

@trumpcrazyaf One of the most important provisions of PODA is a provision that expedites the enforcement of congressional subpoenas.

This would attack the problem of presidents who wish to stonewall all subpoenas.

Another reason we need this bill now.

@LycoPsycho When we get court decisions, they are usually in our favor (holding Congress’s right to testimony).

The problem is how long it takes. This bill goes directly to that problem by expediting court review.

It’s designed to attack the problem of justice delayed being justice denied.

@HTortorici They should. This isn’t a partisan vote.

Many of the provisions in the bill had GOP authorship in the past.

This will test whether Republicans care more about our democracy than they fear the former president.

@softlikewater PODA is the third pillar of our Democracy Agenda.

It's a complement to the John Lewis Voting Rights Act, which was written to put a stop to these truly despicable efforts by the Republican party to suppress the vote.

We need the entire agenda to get the job done.

@alikat747 @BDGarp I hope that some Republicans will sign on, but I know better than to hold my breath.

So we're going to keep pushing to abolish or carve out the filibuster for pro-democracy bills.

Senators who would preserve an archaic rule over our democracy need a serious reality check.

@GovAcctProj PODA enhances protections for whistleblowers.

It also clarifies the right of government workers to provide information directly to Congress and creates a right of action for whistleblowers who are outed by government officials

And that's just a start!

@ArtDevil313 Great point - one that really gets to the heart of this bill.

PODA is designed to close those loopholes and codify those norms, so we can push back meaningfully when a president abuses their power.

And yes, it requires candidates to give their tax returns to the FEC.

Did you know that Louis DeJoy, Trump's hand-picked head of the USPS, is still in charge? And still sabotaging our postal system?
 
@POTUS has worked to remove DeJoy, but Senate Republicans are blocking any progress.
 
We rely on a strong USPS. It’s past time for DeJoy to go.

My heart goes out to Officer Billy Evans’ family, especially his two beautiful children.

@CapitolPolice have endured so much. But they continue to show up every day to protect not just a building, but the democracy it represents.

Rest In Peace, Officer.

I would like to personally welcome our new @HouseIntel members:

@RepJasonCrow, @RepJimCooper, @RepBrianFitz, @RepTrentKelly, @RepLahood, and @RepMullin

We have much to do to keep our country safe. Looking forward to our work together.

It isn’t enough to beat coronavirus. We have a responsibility to learn from our mistakes so we can be better prepared in the future.

@SenFeinstein and I introduced a bill to ensure a comprehensive review of the action—and inaction—that led to this crisis:
https://t.co/ieojdz52Ye

A record-breaking 20.5 million jobs were lost in April. Unemployment has risen to 14.7%.

But mass unemployment is a policy choice. It doesn't have to be this way.

@RepJayapal and I broke down how her Paycheck Guarantee Act will keep people on payroll and businesses afloat: https://t.co/njR1DxkOqj

After 9/11, we established a commission to review why America was so vulnerable to attack and how to protect ourselves going forward.

We need to do the same here.

@RepStephMurphy, @BennieGThompson and I explain why we need a coronavirus commission: https://t.co/VGyUyH2IZK
